				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">MMC3 counts with 8x A12 toggles per line, right?</div>No.  The MMC3's IRQ counter is clocked every time A12 changes from low to high after being low for a certain period of time.  Over the course of a scanline, assuming the PPU is properly configured, A12 will go from low to high eight times.  However, only the first is seen by the MMC3's counter, because the other seven occur too soon after A12 going low.
<br />
<br />A12 needs to be low for around 3 or 4 CPU cycles before the MMC3 will register a clock on the next A12 transition.  (I don't know if the exact timing has been measured or not.)</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />"Last version was better," says Floyd. "More bugs. Bugs make game fun."</div>
