					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What's the best way to get a 113 + 2/3 cycle counter or divider using only Phi2? A 113 cycle counter and a 114 cycle counter which is used every third terminal count?</div>
<br />
<br />Other way around. According to Disch's VRC IRQ page on the nesdevwiki, the Konami VRC mappers that support IRQ (VRC4, VRC6, and VRC7) do something like this when the prescaler is on. Two 114-cycle counts followed by one 113-cycle count, then the counter decrements.</div>

