						<div class="postbody">Just my 2 cents about it, but the simplest way to get a simple and accurate IRQ counter would be to go the A13 way... It normally toggles a fixed number of times each scanline.
<br />The problem with M2 is that it continues to run during VBlank, so software have to first rely on a sprite zero hit or whathever to have a known posision before starting the counting.</div>

