					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That is almost exactly what one of my mmc3 versions looks like.  Only difference is I used a counter instead of the FDC chain. It is probably better to use the on board 20 mhz clock (nesclk) instead of m2 to get more accurate a12 ignore timing.  m2 alignment might be the part making it unreliable.
<br />
<br />I think the correct timing is ignore a12 unless it has been low for 13 or more ppu clock cycles.  That is the time between the last pulse from the sprite fetch to the first pulse from the next scanline bg fetch.  8 ppu clock cycles might also be correct, the time between sprite fetches.
<br />
<br />Writing to $C001 should not cause an IRQ, should be in blargg's irq tests #2 Details.</div>

